17:
SELECT 
(COUNT(*) * 100.0 / (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM connected)) as percentage
FROM connected c
JOIN atom a1 ON c.atom_id = a1.atom_id
JOIN atom a2 ON c.atom_id2 = a2.atom_id
GROUP BY 
    CASE WHEN a1.element <= a2.element 
    THEN a1.element ELSE a2.element END,
    CASE WHEN a1.element <= a2.element 
    THEN a2.element ELSE a1.element END
HAVING COUNT(*) = (
    SELECT COUNT(*) as cnt
    FROM connected c2
    JOIN atom a3 ON c2.atom_id = a3.atom_id
    JOIN atom a4 ON c2.atom_id2 = a4.atom_id
    GROUP BY 
        CASE WHEN a3.element <= a4.element 
        THEN a3.element ELSE a4.element END,
        CASE WHEN a3.element <= a4.element 
        THEN a4.element ELSE a3.element END
    ORDER BY cnt DESC
    LIMIT 1
)	----- bird -----	toxicology

WITH LoansByYear AS (
  SELECT 
    STRFTIME('%Y', l.date) as year,
    SUM(l.amount) as total_amount
  FROM loan l
  JOIN account a ON l.account_id = a.account_id
  JOIN disp d ON a.account_id = d.account_id
  JOIN client c ON d.client_id = c.client_id
  WHERE c.gender = 'M'
  AND STRFTIME('%Y', l.date) IN ('1996', '1997')
  GROUP BY STRFTIME('%Y', l.date)
)
SELECT 
  ROUND(((y2.total_amount - y1.total_amount) * 100.0 / y1.total_amount), 2) as growth_rate
FROM LoansByYear y1
CROSS JOIN LoansByYear y2
WHERE y1.year = '1996'
AND y2.year = '1997'	----- bird -----	financial

WITH yearly_consumption AS (
  SELECT 
    c.Segment,
    SUBSTR(y."Date", 1, 4) as Year,
    SUM(y.Consumption) as total_consumption
  FROM yearmonth y
  JOIN customers c ON y.CustomerID = c.CustomerID
  WHERE c.Currency = 'EUR'
  AND SUBSTR(y."Date", 1, 4) IN ('2012', '2013')
  GROUP BY c.Segment, SUBSTR(y."Date", 1, 4)
),
growth_rates AS (
  SELECT 
    y1.Segment,
    ((y2.total_consumption - y1.total_consumption) / y1.total_consumption * 100) as growth_rate
  FROM yearly_consumption y1
  JOIN yearly_consumption y2 ON y1.Segment = y2.Segment
  WHERE y1.Year = '2012' AND y2.Year = '2013'
)
SELECT Segment, growth_rate
FROM growth_rates
WHERE growth_rate = (SELECT MAX(growth_rate) FROM growth_rates)
   OR growth_rate = (SELECT MIN(growth_rate) FROM growth_rates)
ORDER BY growth_rate DESC	----- bird -----	debit_card_specializing
